WEBVTT

00:01.390 --> 00:03.643
Stella: Previously
on "Life Sentence"...

00:03.690 --> 00:05.033
It's raining...
in our bar!

00:05.090 --> 00:07.172
Half the building
needs new piping.

00:07.220 --> 00:08.824
We gonna need some fast cash
for repairs?

00:08.870 --> 00:10.178
Possibly.

00:10.220 --> 00:11.563
Peter: Can I ask
what's going on

00:11.620 --> 00:13.042
between you
and that doctor?

00:13.100 --> 00:14.090
Stella:
He kissed me last night.

00:14.140 --> 00:15.175
I stopped it.

00:15.230 --> 00:16.482
You'd better
figure this out

00:16.530 --> 00:18.134
before he causes
permanent damage.

00:18.190 --> 00:20.488
There are too many people
in your relationship, Wes.

00:20.540 --> 00:22.019
When you married my daughter,

00:22.060 --> 00:23.539
we had an agreement
you'd take care of her.

00:23.580 --> 00:25.014
And I have.
Really?

00:25.060 --> 00:26.050
By messing around
with your former girlfriend?

00:26.110 --> 00:27.453
You're right.

00:27.500 --> 00:29.013
There are too many people
in this relationship.

00:29.070 --> 00:30.322
Stella: What happened?

00:30.370 --> 00:31.804
Wes: He collapsed
outside our apartment.

00:31.850 --> 00:33.409
Your father's recovering.
The procedure went well.

00:33.460 --> 00:35.155
I still want to make
this work.Stella: So do 1.

00:35.200 --> 00:37.897
But we keep
running into walls.

00:37.950 --> 00:39.816
And I don't know
which way to turn.

00:39.860 --> 00:41.726
Your dad's surgeon
reported me to management,

00:41.780 --> 00:43.771
and the hospital put me
on a temporary suspension.

00:43.820 --> 00:45.948
Me taking a break from here,
it's not a bad thing.

00:55.660 --> 00:59.449
Once upon a time,

00:59.490 --> 01:01.219
all I wanted
was to find someone

01:01.270 --> 01:04.614
who would tell me
he loved me.

01:07.110 --> 01:09.977
But things were simpler
back then.

01:11.200 --> 01:13.976
For one, I was dying...

01:14.030 --> 01:15.156
Peter: It's not over.

01:15.200 --> 01:16.975
There are more aggressive
options.

01:17.030 --> 01:18.896
We've beat this before -- No.

01:18.940 --> 01:20.544
What do you mean "No"?

01:20.600 --> 01:22.113
I don't want to do this
anymore.

01:23.950 --> 01:26.851
It's not working.

01:26.910 --> 01:29.208
And it's really painful
and exhausting.

01:29.260 --> 01:30.989
And doing the same thing
over and over

01:31.040 --> 01:32.121
and expecting
different results,

01:32.170 --> 01:33.649
it's crazy.

01:33.700 --> 01:35.475
Stella, you have
to keep fighting.

01:35.530 --> 01:38.044
If you don't
want the chemo, honey,

01:38.090 --> 01:40.434
we'll find something else.

01:40.490 --> 01:42.219
You can't give up, sis.

01:42.270 --> 01:44.056
I'm not giving up.

01:45.670 --> 01:47.274
I'm giving in...

01:47.320 --> 01:50.278
to fate, to destiny,

01:50.320 --> 01:53.881
to hope that --
that maybe this is

01:53.930 --> 01:56.365
all part of
some greater plan.

01:58.030 --> 01:59.509
I want to do big things

01:59.550 --> 02:03.111
with whatever time
I have left.

02:03.160 --> 02:04.889
I want to climb a mountain.

02:04.950 --> 02:08.853
And I want to stand
under the Eiffel Tower.

02:08.910 --> 02:11.550
And I --
I want to fall in love.

02:13.740 --> 02:15.515
Okay, then.

02:15.570 --> 02:17.345
Let's get you out of here.

02:20.790 --> 02:22.827
But nothing's
that simple anymore.

02:22.880 --> 02:24.097
Will, wait!

02:24.140 --> 02:25.483
Will!

02:27.400 --> 02:29.573
Why are you trying
to ruin my marriage?

02:29.620 --> 02:31.349
Stella,
if your marriage is solid,

02:31.410 --> 02:33.970
then I can't ruin it by --
by telling you how I feel.

02:34.020 --> 02:36.455
I'm sorry, but th-that
is not my fault.

02:36.500 --> 02:39.140
I did not ask you
to fall in love with me.

02:39.200 --> 02:41.020
No, you just made it
impossible not to.

02:41.070 --> 02:42.367
How did I do that?!

02:42.420 --> 02:43.933
By being you, Stella.

02:45.420 --> 02:46.672
Can you please
just be honest with me

02:46.730 --> 02:48.118
about how you feel?

02:49.510 --> 02:50.500
I love Wes.

02:50.560 --> 02:52.119
No.
How you feel about me.

02:55.910 --> 02:57.730
I can't answer that.

02:57.780 --> 02:59.737
Well, then I can't walk away
from this.

02:59.780 --> 03:02.340
Well, maybe youcan't,
but I can.

03:07.140 --> 03:08.528
I said it.

03:08.570 --> 03:10.709
Now all I had to do
is believe it.

03:12.060 --> 03:14.097
Don't worry about a thing

03:14.150 --> 03:17.927
You'll learn to live again

03:17.980 --> 03:19.789
You're gonna learn
to live again

03:19.850 --> 03:23.935
Oh, oh, oh

03:47.220 --> 03:49.268
Stella: Hi.
My name is Stella Jane Abbott.

03:49.310 --> 03:52.484
And if you're watching this,
I'm already dead.

03:52.530 --> 03:54.259
But don't be sad for me.

03:54.320 --> 03:56.004
I had an amazing life.

03:56.060 --> 03:57.312
And before I died,

03:57.360 --> 03:59.920
I got to marry
the man of my dreams.

03:59.970 --> 04:01.620
In fact, my only regret is

04:01.670 --> 04:04.196
that I have to leave him
behind.

04:04.240 --> 04:05.457
Which is why...

04:05.500 --> 04:08.413
I want you
to marry my husband.

04:10.460 --> 04:11.985
This is him --

04:12.030 --> 04:13.282
Wesley Charles.

04:13.340 --> 04:14.466
But it's "Wes" for short.

04:14.510 --> 04:15.284
Although he is not short.

04:15.340 --> 04:16.238
He is 6 feet tall

04:16.290 --> 04:18.110
and has a smile so warm

04:18.170 --> 04:20.161
that it wraps itself
around you.

04:21.339 --> 04:22.512
Here are some things

04:22.560 --> 04:24.073
that I love the most
about him.

04:24.130 --> 04:25.427
He is British,

04:25.480 --> 04:28.086
so his accent adds
this sexy sophistication

04:28.130 --> 04:29.382
to everything he says.

04:29.440 --> 04:30.305
He could be reading
a grocery list,

04:30.350 --> 04:31.784
and you're just like,

04:31.830 --> 04:34.219
"Shut up, why are you so hot
and brilliant?"

04:34.270 --> 04:36.307
He's a crazy romantic.

04:36.360 --> 04:38.010
And when he looks at you,

04:38.060 --> 04:40.404
the whole world
just falls away.

04:41.890 --> 04:44.313
Basically,
he is the greatest man

04:44.370 --> 04:45.883
I have ever known.

04:47.540 --> 04:49.759
So, if you think
you are deserving

04:49.810 --> 04:51.892
of marrying a man
like my husband,

04:51.940 --> 04:53.374
then you need to speak up

04:53.420 --> 04:58.768
and let him know
that it's okay to love again.

04:58.820 --> 05:01.721
And, Wes,
if you're watching this,

05:01.770 --> 05:05.126
my hope for you is
a long, amazing life,

05:05.170 --> 05:07.423
so full of happiness

05:07.480 --> 05:09.209
that you forget
all about me...

05:10.480 --> 05:13.916
...until one day
when we meet again.

05:13.960 --> 05:16.429
For now and always...

05:16.490 --> 05:18.652
I love you.

05:22.710 --> 05:24.405
Stella:
I forgot I made that.

05:24.450 --> 05:28.364
I set it to post
after I was sure that I'd...

05:28.410 --> 05:31.630
That is the nicest thing

05:31.670 --> 05:34.105
anyone's ever done
for me.

05:37.550 --> 05:39.894
I love you.

05:39.940 --> 05:42.079
I love you, too.

05:51.650 --> 05:53.607
Why are you crying?

05:53.650 --> 05:55.789
I came so close
to losing my dad,

05:55.830 --> 05:58.390
and it just...

05:58.440 --> 06:01.660
reminded me of how
not ready I am to lose him.

06:04.790 --> 06:06.394
Or you.

06:08.970 --> 06:11.359
He is not going anywhere,
okay?

06:14.060 --> 06:15.494
And neither am I.

06:27.820 --> 06:29.640
I can't believe we
almost lost him.

06:33.480 --> 06:34.902
I can't believe

06:34.950 --> 06:36.429
that we found a worse way
to spend the night

06:36.480 --> 06:38.437
than sitting through
a kindergarten play.

06:38.480 --> 06:41.211
Tell me how to be
in this world

06:41.270 --> 06:44.570
Tell me how to breathe in
and feel no hurt

06:44.620 --> 06:47.009
Tell me how,
'cause I believe in something

06:48.100 --> 06:51.445
I believe in us

06:51.490 --> 06:53.447
Tell me when the light
goes out As the next few days passed,

06:53.500 --> 06:55.104
we all took shifts
taking care of my dad.

06:55.150 --> 06:56.663
That even in the dark
we will find a way out

06:56.720 --> 06:58.370
But he wasn't the only one
in that room

06:58.410 --> 07:00.014
who was trying to recover.

07:00.070 --> 07:02.289
Tell me how,
'cause I believe in something

07:02.330 --> 07:05.675
I believe in us

07:08.470 --> 07:12.373
We used to be kids
living just for kicks

07:13.650 --> 07:17.120
In cinema seats
learning how to kiss

07:18.610 --> 07:22.046
Running through streets
that were painted gold

07:22.090 --> 07:25.651
We never believed
we'd grow up like this

07:25.700 --> 07:28.431
So tell me how to be
in this world

07:28.490 --> 07:30.481
Tell me how to breathe in
and feel no hurt

07:30.530 --> 07:31.747
Dr. Ackerman:
I have some good news.

07:31.790 --> 07:33.189
Tell me how Mr. Abbott...

07:33.230 --> 07:34.743
"Cause I believe
in something

07:34.800 --> 07:36.052
...your vitals are strong
and consistent enough

07:36.100 --> 07:37.579
that I can send you
home tomorrow.

07:37.630 --> 07:38.665
I believe in us Wes: How about that?

07:38.710 --> 07:40.053
-Oh, my God!

07:40.110 --> 07:42.067
Tell me when the light
goes down

07:42.110 --> 07:45.410
That even in the dark
we will find a way out

07:45.460 --> 07:48.373
Tell me now,
'cause I believe in something

07:48.420 --> 07:49.581
I believe in

07:49.640 --> 07:51.722
I believe in us

07:51.770 --> 07:53.022
I believe in

07:53.080 --> 07:55.026
I believe in something

07:55.080 --> 07:56.115
I believe

07:56.170 --> 07:59.947
I believe in us

08:01.740 --> 08:02.957
Aiden: I took them
all out of hiding,

08:03.000 --> 08:04.479
so you wouldn't be
startled

08:04.520 --> 08:05.828
and have another
heart attack.

08:06.740 --> 08:08.083
All right, well,
let's get this party started.

08:08.130 --> 08:09.177
Come on.

08:11.620 --> 08:13.270
Peter:
Who wants gnome cake?

08:14.660 --> 08:16.059
Thanks for today.

08:16.100 --> 08:18.660
I really appreciate
you being there for me.

08:18.710 --> 08:20.018
We're always
here for you.

08:20.060 --> 08:21.141
No matter what.

08:22.370 --> 08:23.587
I'm glad you feel that way,

08:23.630 --> 08:24.791
because I have something
to tell you...

08:25.760 --> 08:27.671
I'm gonna pop
the question!

08:28.680 --> 08:32.116
Dad,
you and Gina just met.

08:32.159 --> 08:33.889
And you're crushing it
with the ladies.

08:33.940 --> 08:36.898
Not the time to commit,
playa!

08:36.950 --> 08:39.032
Playa's already committed.

08:39.080 --> 08:41.390
But not to Gina.

08:41.429 --> 08:42.773
I'm talking about
your mother.

08:44.300 --> 08:45.779
I'm gonna win her back.

08:50.260 --> 08:53.264
Do you think Mom
wants to come back?I don't know.

08:53.310 --> 08:55.085
But I just realized
that when she left me...

08:55.140 --> 08:57.040
I fought withher,

08:57.100 --> 08:58.522
but I never really
fought forher.

08:58.580 --> 09:00.662
Let's not forget,
Mom's a bi...

09:00.710 --> 09:02.314
That means
I've got a 50/50 shot.

09:02.360 --> 09:03.703
I'll take those odds.

09:03.760 --> 09:05.979
Mm, don't really think
it works that way.

09:06.020 --> 09:08.580
Dad, what about Gina?

09:08.630 --> 09:10.280
I have to break up
with her.

09:10.330 --> 09:11.934
I have to listen
to my heart.

09:11.980 --> 09:13.846
That's what this second chance
is for me.

09:13.900 --> 09:15.413
It's a chance for me
to listen,

09:15.460 --> 09:19.590
to show your mom
that I can do that now.

09:19.640 --> 09:21.028
But I'm gonna need
your help.

09:21.080 --> 09:24.425
Tomorrow night...
at our anniversary party.

09:24.470 --> 09:27.690
You're not having
an anniversary party.Yes, we are.

09:27.740 --> 09:29.083
And you're throwing it.

09:29.130 --> 09:30.291
Ah.

09:30.350 --> 09:33.604
So...we'll do it at the bar,
Aiden?

09:33.660 --> 09:34.991
Yep.

09:35.050 --> 09:36.825
Lizzie, you can help me
with my speech...

09:36.880 --> 09:38.359
Peter:
...and, Stella...

09:38.400 --> 09:40.300
you can make it romantic --

09:40.360 --> 09:42.749
candles, flowers,
the whole shebang.

09:42.790 --> 09:45.407
Dad,

09:45.450 --> 09:47.578
I've never been
more sure of anything.

09:47.630 --> 09:50.144
Part of me
thought he was crazy.

09:50.190 --> 09:51.749
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
over P.A. ]

09:51.800 --> 09:54.144
But I guess I used to be
that crazy, too.

09:54.200 --> 09:55.713
Wes: You sure about this?

09:55.760 --> 09:56.932
I have never been
more sure

09:56.980 --> 09:58.288
about anything
in my life.

09:58.330 --> 09:59.980
My family is gonna
fall in love with you.

10:00.030 --> 10:01.805
I just feel like
we should have given them

10:01.860 --> 10:03.464
a heads up
that we were engaged...

10:03.510 --> 10:04.409
or that I exist.

10:04.470 --> 10:06.598
Diego: There she is!

10:06.640 --> 10:08.426
Oh, she looks
SO grown up.

10:08.470 --> 10:09.642
Stella!Hi!

10:09.690 --> 10:12.296
Welcome home!

10:12.350 --> 10:14.250
Oh.

10:14.300 --> 10:15.995
Who is this?

10:16.050 --> 10:19.042
Thisis Wes.

10:19.090 --> 10:20.910
Hi. Very nice to meet
all of you.

10:20.960 --> 10:22.871
Oh, he's British, isn't he?

10:22.920 --> 10:25.617
Yes, Mom.
And he's also amazing.

10:28.320 --> 10:29.924
And he's my fianc.

10:30.930 --> 10:32.273
We got engaged!

10:32.320 --> 10:34.186
It was so romantic... Oh!

10:34.240 --> 10:35.537
He --Oh, my --

10:35.590 --> 10:36.807
Daddy.

10:36.850 --> 10:38.102
Stella: You okay?

10:38.150 --> 10:40.585
It's just...
all happening so fast.

10:40.640 --> 10:44.634
Well, it's not like
I can really take my time.

10:46.730 --> 10:48.243
Congratulations.

10:53.910 --> 10:56.823
Seeing my father make the most
of his second chance

10:56.870 --> 10:59.692
made me wonder if I was making
the most of mine.

11:00.960 --> 11:03.304
Okay, so that was Gina
on the phone.

11:03.350 --> 11:04.875
