14:10.060 --> 14:11.448
And I hate when you accuse
me of freaking out when I'm not,

14:11.500 --> 14:12.843
because that makes me
freak out,

14:12.890 --> 14:14.278
so it turns into some
self-fulfilling prophecy

14:14.330 --> 14:15.889
where I act like
a lunatic. Stella.

14:15.940 --> 14:17.066
What?We're still live.

14:17.110 --> 14:18.498
Oh, crap.

14:26.210 --> 14:27.598
Stell,
what are you doing?

14:27.640 --> 14:28.812
Responding to all

14:28.860 --> 14:30.771
these ridiculous comments
on our video

14:30.820 --> 14:32.470
about how we clearly
weren't planning on

14:32.520 --> 14:33.908
having an actual future
together.

14:35.300 --> 14:38.600
Well...we weren't,
were we?

14:38.660 --> 14:39.957
No.

14:40.000 --> 14:41.217
But now we are...

14:41.270 --> 14:44.092
so we will figure it out,
Hater282.

14:48.490 --> 14:49.924
We'll figure it out,
right?

14:49.970 --> 14:52.314
Of course we will.

14:52.360 --> 14:54.180
So let's talk about it.

14:54.240 --> 14:56.231
Our future --
Let's figure it out.

14:56.280 --> 14:57.236
Right now?

14:57.280 --> 14:58.839
Seems like a lot to go into

14:58.890 --> 14:59.937
before we've even
had coffee.

15:01.200 --> 15:03.100
I just feel all this
crazy pressure.

15:03.160 --> 15:04.503
I'm not pressuring you.

15:04.550 --> 15:06.461
Well, that doesn't stop me
from feeling it.

15:06.510 --> 15:08.285
And it doesn't stop them
from mocking us.

15:10.120 --> 15:12.555
It's about the bar.

15:12.600 --> 15:13.726
I forgot I have a meeting

15:13.780 --> 15:15.123
with a potential buyer
today.

15:15.170 --> 15:16.205
Yeah, go ahead.

15:16.260 --> 15:18.035
I'll just be here.

15:20.000 --> 15:21.786
Defending our marriage.

15:27.010 --> 15:28.910
Wes, hey!

15:28.970 --> 15:30.870
Your friend here
was just telling me

15:30.930 --> 15:32.967
his company may be
interested in your offer

15:33.010 --> 15:34.353
to sell the bar.

15:34.410 --> 15:36.014
Richard: Now, I'm gonna
go through the numbers

15:36.060 --> 15:37.403
and be in touch.

15:37.450 --> 15:39.361
Oh, great.
Thank you so much, Richard.

15:39.410 --> 15:41.196
Yeah,
thanks a million, Dick!

15:43.550 --> 15:44.711
You were gonna sell my bar

15:44.760 --> 15:45.898
without talking to me
first?

15:45.940 --> 15:47.066
Okay. Ourbar.

15:47.120 --> 15:48.679
And I'm sorry
I didn't tell you,

15:48.730 --> 15:50.721
but Richard's company
could take over our lease,

15:50.770 --> 15:51.987
and pay back the debt --

15:52.030 --> 15:53.247
So we walk away
with nothing

15:53.300 --> 15:54.506
but your stupid
sex painting?

15:54.560 --> 15:55.982
Yes.

15:56.040 --> 15:57.690
I know that is
a sex painting.

15:57.730 --> 16:00.074
And while I am grossed out,
because it's my sister,

16:00.130 --> 16:01.609
I have to admit
it's kind of cool,

16:01.650 --> 16:03.345
and I can't believe
I've never made one.

16:03.390 --> 16:06.610
Aiden, look, we can't reopen
without running water.

16:06.660 --> 16:08.526
So, what would you say
if, uh --

16:08.570 --> 16:10.481
if I found the money?

16:10.530 --> 16:12.578
I would say
that you have robbed a bank,

16:12.620 --> 16:14.440
or you've made a deal
with a dark wizard,

16:14.490 --> 16:16.447
because there is literally
nothing I haven't tried.

16:16.490 --> 16:17.571
Are you sure
you're not just

16:17.620 --> 16:19.145
giving up
on this partnership,

16:19.190 --> 16:21.534
because you're worried about
your other partnership?

16:21.580 --> 16:23.969
And I'm not giving up
this place.

16:24.020 --> 16:27.320
So...I'm gonna find
another way.

16:27.370 --> 16:29.839
Be my guest.

16:31.120 --> 16:33.020
Hey, sis.

16:33.070 --> 16:34.549
I will need
one free coffee

16:34.600 --> 16:36.079
and a free muffin stat.

16:36.120 --> 16:38.680
You do realize
I'm standing right here.

16:38.730 --> 16:40.289
I do,
but I am broke and hungry.

16:40.340 --> 16:41.466
- Plus I have
an important meeting

16:41.520 --> 16:42.464
with a potential
investor.

16:42.520 --> 16:44.124
That's great.Seriously?

16:44.170 --> 16:46.036
Who would be rich enough
and dumb enough

16:46.090 --> 16:47.125
to invest in you?

16:49.610 --> 16:51.829
Oh, my God, Stella!

16:51.880 --> 16:53.689
Marlene.
Hey!

16:55.270 --> 16:56.396
You better ask her
for money fast,

16:56.450 --> 16:57.781
before she ruins
my floors.

16:57.840 --> 16:59.831
My water just broke.

16:59.880 --> 17:01.223
Too late.

17:01.280 --> 17:03.089
Uh...do you need a ride
to the hospital?

17:03.150 --> 17:04.276
Um...

17:04.319 --> 17:05.105
You don't have a car.

17:05.150 --> 17:06.584
Or a license.

17:06.630 --> 17:07.665
Huh?

17:10.940 --> 17:13.238
Aiden: All right, baby on board.
Let's do this.

17:13.290 --> 17:15.804
Stella: Good luck.

17:15.859 --> 17:17.510
Dr. Grant: Stella.

17:17.550 --> 17:19.461
Hey, can we talk?

17:19.510 --> 17:20.853
There's nothing left
to talk about.

17:20.900 --> 17:22.777
I think I made that
perfectly clear.

17:22.819 --> 17:24.810
I don't think that we should
even see each other anymore.

17:24.859 --> 17:25.998
Okay, well,
that shouldn't be a problem.

17:27.390 --> 17:28.733
I'm leaving Asheville
tonight.

17:28.780 --> 17:31.306
Do you...
just have five minutes

17:31.350 --> 17:32.738
SO we can say goodbye?

17:34.830 --> 17:36.264
So, where are you going?

17:36.310 --> 17:38.130
Papua New Guinea.

17:38.180 --> 17:40.786
People don't go
to Papua New Guinea.

17:40.840 --> 17:42.137
Well, they do

17:42.190 --> 17:43.999
if Doctors Without Borders
stations them there.

17:45.540 --> 17:46.757
Truth is, this is something

17:46.800 --> 17:47.961
I've always wanted to do,
you know,

17:48.020 --> 17:49.363
help people
that really needed me,

17:49.410 --> 17:50.627
to go see the world.

17:52.280 --> 17:55.671
Well,
that sounds amazing.

17:56.640 --> 17:57.801
Come with me.

18:03.770 --> 18:05.204
I can't come with you.

18:05.250 --> 18:06.809
My whole life is here.

18:06.860 --> 18:08.168
No, Stella,
your past is here.

18:08.210 --> 18:10.998
But your future
could be bigger than this.

18:11.040 --> 18:12.292
Great.

18:12.350 --> 18:14.307
So, you saw me freak out
on social media

18:14.350 --> 18:15.863
about my life
being too small and --

18:15.920 --> 18:17.604
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

18:17.660 --> 18:21.096
You can't expect me
to pack up my life and --

18:21.140 --> 18:23.393
and leave with you
tonight.

18:23.450 --> 18:26.613
This is the real world.
It's not a movie.

18:26.670 --> 18:29.139
I'm not asking you
to come tonight.

18:29.190 --> 18:31.238
You can come
whenever you're ready.

18:31.280 --> 18:33.317
You know,
stay as long as you want.

18:33.370 --> 18:35.452
I'm not asking you
to marry me.

18:35.500 --> 18:37.491
I'm just --

18:37.550 --> 18:38.972
I'm asking you to live.

18:42.460 --> 18:45.020
Oh, and, uh,
for the record,

18:45.080 --> 18:47.686
there's nothing wrong
with living in a movie.

18:58.570 --> 19:00.607
What if Will was right?

19:00.660 --> 19:02.139
What if my future

19:02.180 --> 19:04.524
was supposed to be
bigger than this?

19:04.570 --> 19:05.617
What if...

19:05.660 --> 19:06.741
Sadie: Stella.

19:06.790 --> 19:08.042
Stella: Sadie.
Hey.

19:08.100 --> 19:09.352
What are you doing here?

19:09.400 --> 19:10.356
I leave for Seattle today

19:10.410 --> 19:11.923
for the rest of the trial,

19:11.970 --> 19:13.313
so my Aunt Cindy and I
wanted to come see you.

19:13.360 --> 19:15.704
Because you took
such good care of our girl,

19:15.760 --> 19:17.535
I was able to save up
enough vacation time

19:17.590 --> 19:18.534
to go with her,

19:18.590 --> 19:20.240
so thank you.

19:21.810 --> 19:23.062
Well, most of the time,

19:23.110 --> 19:25.249
it felt like
she was taking care of me.

19:25.290 --> 19:26.371
Because I was.

19:26.420 --> 19:27.854
Stella's a hot mess.

19:27.900 --> 19:29.766
We should probably get going.

19:29.820 --> 19:31.163
I'll meet you at the car?

19:31.210 --> 19:32.166
Yeah.Bye-bye.

19:32.210 --> 19:34.076
Bye.

19:36.780 --> 19:38.293
I don't want
to say goodbye,

19:38.350 --> 19:40.000
'cause it feels like
bad luck.

19:40.040 --> 19:44.216
Sadie, you're gonna make it
through this trial.

19:44.270 --> 19:45.999
And you are
going to graduate

19:46.050 --> 19:47.779
from high school
with honors,

19:47.830 --> 19:49.650
and go to college
somewhere warm and sunny,

19:49.710 --> 19:52.179
and you're probably
gonna become a doctor.

19:52.230 --> 19:53.743
Or president.

19:53.800 --> 19:55.484
Or a doctor president.

19:55.540 --> 19:57.793
You have an oddly clear vision
of my future.

19:57.840 --> 20:00.662
Yeah.

20:00.720 --> 20:03.621
Now I just need one
for my own.

20:03.680 --> 20:05.546
Well, thanks for
believing in me.

20:05.590 --> 20:07.240
And for being
my best friend.

20:07.290 --> 20:09.019
Fun fact --

20:09.070 --> 20:11.983
when we first met,
I didn't even like you.

20:16.300 --> 20:17.552
Come here.

20:18.300 --> 20:19.290
Thank you.

20:19.340 --> 20:20.819
There you go.

20:20.870 --> 20:22.258
There?
Wes: Uh-huh.

20:23.220 --> 20:24.563
Again.

20:24.610 --> 20:27.307
Hey!

20:27.350 --> 20:29.170
He isn't supposed
to see the bride

20:29.220 --> 20:30.745
before the wedding.Mm.

20:30.790 --> 20:33.521
We're not really worried
about bad luck.

20:33.580 --> 20:34.615
Let me do that.

20:34.660 --> 20:36.355
The ceremony starts in 20.

20:36.400 --> 20:38.357
All right.
See you out there.

20:38.410 --> 20:40.060
You most certainly will.

20:43.150 --> 20:44.276
Wes --
I know.

20:46.240 --> 20:47.844
You don't like me.

20:47.890 --> 20:49.892
It's not
that I don't like you.

20:49.940 --> 20:52.250
It's just,

20:52.290 --> 20:53.678
I've spent
the past eight years

20:53.730 --> 20:57.075
trying to prepare myself
for the fact

20:57.120 --> 20:58.895
that I might lose
my little girl.

20:58.950 --> 21:04.127
And now I feel like
I'm losing her twice.

21:07.780 --> 21:09.430
I get that.

21:09.480 --> 21:12.347
I will take care of her,
Mr. Abbott.

21:12.400 --> 21:14.619
I will give Stella
a lifetime of love

21:14.660 --> 21:16.480
over these next
eight months.

21:19.930 --> 21:22.490
In that case...

21:22.540 --> 21:24.497
welcome to the family,
son.

21:32.070 --> 21:33.322
Ah.

21:33.370 --> 21:34.713
This place
is looking great!

21:34.770 --> 21:35.931
Ah.

21:35.990 --> 21:38.504
Perfect for sweeping Ida
off her feet.

21:38.550 --> 21:41.156
I really hope
she says yes.

21:41.210 --> 21:43.338
I could use
the inspiration.

21:45.730 --> 21:46.811
What's goin' on?

21:46.870 --> 21:48.258
Oh, no, nothing.
Nothing.

21:48.300 --> 21:51.474
I just, um...

21:51.520 --> 21:54.342
It's just what you said
about me and Stella.

21:54.400 --> 21:55.470
I just --

21:55.530 --> 21:57.567
I feel like
I'm failing her.

21:57.620 --> 21:59.964
I don't know.
Hey.

22:00.010 --> 22:01.353
You saved her.

22:01.400 --> 22:03.004
You're the reason

22:03.060 --> 22:04.744
she agreed to do
the clinical trial.

22:04.800 --> 22:06.529
If it wasn't for you,

22:06.580 --> 22:08.184
we'd all have lost her.

22:08.230 --> 22:10.665
I still might.

22:10.720 --> 22:12.370
I've tried everything
I can think of

22:12.410 --> 22:13.969
to make her happy.

22:14.020 --> 22:17.103
But I know she's questioning
her future with me.

22:17.160 --> 22:21.245
You know,
when Ida and I got married,

22:21.290 --> 22:23.896
everything we had
was old and borrowed.

22:23.950 --> 22:26.510
The only thing blue was
the discount tux I wore.

22:28.340 --> 22:29.774
For our something new,

22:29.820 --> 22:31.549
Ida asked me to get these
specific champagne flutes

22:31.610 --> 22:32.907
for the toast.

22:32.960 --> 22:35.566
So, I went to get them.

22:35.610 --> 22:38.693
But then I saw these expensive
Waterford crystal ones.

22:38.740 --> 22:40.469
And I decided to show off.

22:42.620 --> 22:46.443
Well, later, I realized
the flutes she asked me for

22:46.490 --> 22:47.969
were the same kind

22:48.010 --> 22:50.058
her grandparents toasted with
at their wedding.

22:52.450 --> 22:55.408
But I couldn't
see that then,

22:55.460 --> 22:57.588
because I was too wrapped up
in my own idea

22:57.630 --> 22:59.416
of what would
make her happy.

23:00.980 --> 23:02.379
So...

23:02.420 --> 23:05.026
This time...

23:06.640 --> 23:09.428
...I'm getting
out of the way.

23:14.390 --> 23:16.427
Wow.

23:16.480 --> 23:19.177
Son, there are times
when the person you love

23:19.220 --> 23:23.305
is telling you
exactly what they need.

23:23.350 --> 23:24.875
You just have to listen.

23:28.360 --> 23:30.260
Aiden:
So, that's my pitch.

23:30.320 --> 23:32.539
Considering the high volume
of foot traffic,

23:32.580 --> 23:33.968
the POS retail channel,

23:34.020 --> 23:35.795
not to mention certain
non-liquid assets

23:35.840 --> 23:37.797
like my face and body,

23:37.850 --> 23:39.272
I think we got
a real chance

23:39.330 --> 23:40.809
to do something
special here. Got it.

23:40.850 --> 23:42.454
Fantastic presentation.

23:42.500 --> 23:43.763
So, what do you say?
Are you in?

23:45.240 --> 23:47.288
Yeah, I can't.

23:47.330 --> 23:48.286
Come on. Why not?

23:49.470 --> 23:51.461
I'm sorry.
This is your moment.

23:51.510 --> 23:53.467
And you are gonna
crush it in there.

23:53.510 --> 23:54.648
Do you want me to come in,
or...?

23:54.690 --> 23:57.204
Uh, no,
I'm gonna be fine.

23:57.260 --> 23:59.297
And so are you.

24:03.390 --> 24:05.256
So, I'm gonna go
find a doctor

24:05.310 --> 24:07.950
so they can officially
pronounce my dreams dead.

24:08.010 --> 24:11.833
Hey, for what it's worth,
I was impressed, too.

24:11.880 --> 24:13.097
You know your stuff.

24:13.140 --> 24:14.960
Thanks.

24:15.010 --> 24:16.489
You know, it's funny.

24:16.540 --> 24:17.883
My whole life,

24:17.930 --> 24:19.364
I've basically
been handed everything,

24:19.410 --> 24:21.014
and the one time
I work hard for something,

24:21.060 --> 24:22.403
I don't get to keep it.

24:22.460 --> 24:24.189
Hey, maybe the investor
you're looking for

24:24.240 --> 24:25.321
is right
around the corner.

24:26.550 --> 24:28.029
You and me, we could be

24:28.070 --> 24:29.629
Look at you two.

24:29.680 --> 24:31.637
Something extraordinary Still together.

24:31.680 --> 24:33.466
Must be so easy to be happy

24:33.510 --> 24:35.421
when your smiles
are painted on.

24:35.470 --> 24:37.370
Elizabeth: Do you think
they have carrot ginger cake?

24:37.430 --> 24:39.683
Let me guess,
you're looking for a --

24:39.730 --> 24:42.119
Hey, it's you.

24:42.170 --> 24:44.161
You're the girl
I gave a free cake to

24:44.220 --> 24:46.564
because you were dying.

24:46.610 --> 24:49.523
Oh, man,
why am I so gullible?

24:49.570 --> 24:51.527
Oh, no! I was dying.

24:51.570 --> 24:54.392
But I got better.

24:54.440 --> 24:57.137
Anyway,
I need an anniversary cake.

24:57.190 --> 24:58.578
Anniversary?

24:58.620 --> 25:01.578
That is awesome!

25:01.630 --> 25:03.530
The thought of
your beautiful cancer movie

25:03.580 --> 25:04.661
coming to an end

25:04.720 --> 25:06.666
really broke my heart.

25:06.720 --> 25:08.279
But now that you're hitting
this milestone,

25:08.330 --> 25:09.934
that's just, um...

25:11.330 --> 25:13.321
You know what?

25:13.380 --> 25:15.633
I'm gonna give you
another free cake.

25:17.600 --> 25:18.635
We'll take that one.

25:18.690 --> 25:20.340
Okay. I'll box it up.

25:21.600 --> 25:22.681
Elizabeth: Hey.

25:22.730 --> 25:23.902
What is happening?

25:26.220 --> 25:27.426
I'm...

25:27.480 --> 25:28.902
I'm just not sure
that Wes and I

25:28.960 --> 25:30.564
are gonna make it
to a year.

25:30.610 --> 25:32.521
I just --

25:32.570 --> 25:33.878
I don't know what our future
looks like.

25:33.920 --> 25:36.617
I-I can't even
imagine it.

25:36.660 --> 25:41.222
Well, maybe that's because
you haven't really tried.

25:41.270 --> 25:43.181
Everything you've done
since you were cured

25:43.230 --> 25:45.540
has been kind of...

25:45.580 --> 25:46.661
a stall.

25:47.890 --> 25:49.790
No, it hasn't.
Stell.

25:49.850 --> 25:51.807
You took the first job
you could find.

25:51.850 --> 25:55.457
You focused on your marriage
instead of yourself.

25:55.510 --> 25:57.899
If you really want
to figure things out,

25:57.940 --> 25:59.851
you might just need to be
selfish for a minute.

25:59.900 --> 26:01.629
I can't be selfish.

26:03.030 --> 26:04.987
There's too many people
to take into consideration.

26:05.040 --> 26:06.815
People that have sacrificed
too much for me --

26:06.860 --> 26:08.077
Hey, listen to me.

26:08.130 --> 26:09.382
You owe it to yourself

26:09.430 --> 26:10.909
to make the most
of your second chance,

26:10.960 --> 26:12.906
whatever that means,

26:12.960 --> 26:14.780
because if you don't,

26:14.830 --> 26:16.821
everything we all did
to get you here

26:16.870 --> 26:19.487
will have been
for nothing.

26:24.880 --> 26:28.623
[ Old Sea Brigade's
"Cover My Own" plays ]

26:28.670 --> 26:30.445
That night,
it felt like it took an hour

26:30.500 --> 26:33.276
to walk the 31 steps
to Wee's bar.

26:33.330 --> 26:35.059
My conversation with Lizzie

26:35.110 --> 26:37.363
started so many things
rattling around in my head.

26:37.420 --> 26:38.717
If I really try

26:38.770 --> 26:40.283
Heartbreaker's
always on my mind

26:40.330 --> 26:42.549
Why could I only see
the past with Wes

26:42.600 --> 26:45.558
and not the future?

26:48.820 --> 26:49.901
And what about Will?

26:49.950 --> 26:51.816
Cover my own

26:53.430 --> 26:54.955
Cover my head

26:55.000 --> 26:56.900
What do I want
my life to be?

26:56.960 --> 26:58.917
Thoughts of confusion

27:00.480 --> 27:02.084
Running in my ribs

27:02.140 --> 27:04.131
Where do I even start?

27:04.180 --> 27:05.784
Cover my own

27:12.190 --> 27:13.362
Hey.

27:13.410 --> 27:14.536
Hi.

27:16.110 --> 27:18.408
Peter: All right, your mother
will be here any minute.

27:18.460 --> 27:20.326
I think you should all hide
when she gets here,

27:20.370 --> 27:22.589
so she doesn't feel like
she's being ambushed.

27:22.640 --> 27:24.199
When do you want us
to come out?

27:24.250 --> 27:27.151
Uh, right after
she says "yes."

27:27.210 --> 27:29.941
And what if
she doesn't say yes?

27:29.990 --> 27:31.469
You stay
in your hiding place

27:31.510 --> 27:32.727
until I die
of embarrassment

27:32.780 --> 27:34.123
or you die
of natural causes.

27:34.170 --> 27:35.649
Whichever comes first.

27:35.690 --> 27:37.249
You feeling okay,
Daddy?

27:37.300 --> 27:38.859
Just nervous.

27:38.910 --> 27:40.730
Why? It's not like
it's the first time

27:40.780 --> 27:41.861
you asked Mom
